{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Build Photodump Gallery SaaS Web App for Photo Booth Studios (MVP)\n\nCreate a multi-tenant, end-to-end workflow from photo intake to background application to delivery, aligned to the existing `photo-dump-gallery` codebase. The MVP must support one tenant with real capture/upload, background application, export, analytics, and subscription gating.\n\n**Technical Implementation**\n- Frontend: Web app for operators and kiosk/capture UI. Use browser MediaDevices API for camera capture, plus drag-drop uploads with client-side validation and preview.\n- Backend: REST or typed RPC API (match current stack) with multi-tenant scoping on every request. Async job processing for image composition and export.\n- Storage: S3-compatible object storage (AWS S3/R2/MinIO). Use per-tenant prefixes and pre-signed URLs for direct uploads and downloads.\n- Image processing: Use `sharp` for resizing, compositing, and format conversions. Template-driven composition for single, collage, and strip layouts.\n- AI backgrounds: Integrate a provider (OpenAI/Replicate/Stable Diffusion API) with moderation checks and prompt safety. Cache generations per prompt+params.\n- Billing: Stripe subscriptions with webhook handling and plan-based access control.\n- Analytics: Store events and daily aggregates in the primary DB; expose usage and revenue metrics.\n\n**Core Data Model (suggested tables)**\n- `tenants`, `users`, `roles`, `tenant_members`\n- `photos` (status, original_url, metadata, size, tenant_id, created_by)\n- `backgrounds` (type: curated/ai, prompt, params, asset_url)\n- `compositions` (layout, inputs, output_url, status, cost, created_at)\n- `exports` (format, resolution, output_url, status, expires_at)\n- `subscriptions` (stripe_customer_id, plan, status, renew_at)\n- `usage_counters` (tenant_id, period, ai_generations, exports, storage_bytes)\n- `events` (type, payload, tenant_id, created_at)\n\n**API Contracts (examples)**\n- `POST /api/uploads/sign` → `{url, fields, objectKey}` for direct upload\n- `POST /api/photos` → create photo record with uploaded object key\n- `POST /api/backgrounds/ai` → `{prompt, params}` returns `background_id` (queued)\n- `POST /api/compositions` → `{photo_ids, background_id, layout, options}` returns `composition_id`\n- `POST /api/exports` → `{composition_id, format, resolution}` returns `export_id`\n- `GET /api/dashboard/metrics?from&to` → usage + revenue metrics\n- `POST /api/stripe/webhook` for subscription state changes\n\n**Workflow**\n- Intake: Capture/upload → validate → store original → create `photos` record\n- Background: Choose curated or AI → generate or fetch → store `backgrounds` record\n- Composition: Apply layout + background → async job creates `compositions` output\n- Export: Async job creates output format(s) → signed URL delivery → optional print stub\n\n**Performance & Reliability**\n- Direct-to-storage uploads to avoid server bottlenecks\n- Async queue for AI generation, composition, export (BullMQ/Cloud Tasks/Sidekiq equivalent)\n- Image size limits and streaming uploads\n- Result caching for repeated AI prompts and composition templates\n- Idempotency keys on create endpoints to prevent duplicate jobs\n\n**Security & Multi-Tenancy**\n- Tenant-scoped authorization on every query\n- Row-level constraints in DB queries (tenant_id)\n- Signed URLs with short TTL and tenant-specific prefixes\n- Webhook signature verification for billing\n- Content moderation for AI prompts and generated images\n\n**Edge Cases & Error Handling**\n- Large uploads: chunking, resumable uploads, retry with backoff\n- Camera failures: fallback to file upload; device capability checks\n- AI failures: retry policy, safe fallback to curated backgrounds, surface errors\n- Retention expiry mid-session: warn and block export if inputs expired\n- Export timeouts: job cancellation + retry; partial result cleanup\n- Concurrent sessions: lock per composition job or use queue de-duplication\n- Billing failures: read-only mode or block new creations; clear messaging\n\n**Retention & Quotas**\n- 15-day deletion via bucket lifecycle policy and/or scheduled cleanup job\n- Daily/monthly AI generation quotas enforced with `usage_counters`\n- Storage quota tracking with warnings and hard limits per plan\n\n**Integration Points**\n- Printing: define `PrintProvider` interface with stub implementation (e.g., `createPrintJob`, `getStatus`)\n- Analytics: optionally export events to a warehouse later; keep DB aggregates now\n\n**Implementation Breakdown**\n1. Codebase analysis: identify framework, routing, ORM, auth, storage integration.\n2. Multi-tenant auth: tenant membership, RBAC, request scoping middleware.\n3. Storage + retention: S3 bucket, signed upload, lifecycle policy, cleanup job.\n4. Photo intake: capture UI, upload flow, server validation, metadata persistence.\n5. Backgrounds: curated library CRUD, AI generation pipeline with moderation.\n6. Composition templates: server-side layout engine using `sharp`.\n7. Export pipeline: async jobs, format conversions, delivery URLs.\n8. Billing: Stripe setup, subscription gating, webhooks.\n9. Dashboard: metrics endpoints, widgets, date-range filtering.\n10. Observability: structured logs, job status tracking, failure alerts.\n\n**Success Criteria**\n- 15-day auto-deletion verified via lifecycle policy and cleanup audits\n- AI generation quotas enforced per tenant\n- Exports available as JPEG/PNG/PDF with consistent presets\n- Dashboard shows photos created, clients served, revenue for date range\n- Subscription inactive blocks new creations and exports",
